# core-contract

Defines the ts-rest API consumed by `core-service`, `core-ui`, and `test/`.

## File layout

- `src/contract.ts` — aggregates all routes into one router
- `src/{domain}.ts` — per-domain Zod schemas + route definitions (launches, tests, test-steps, statuses, auth)
- `src/defaults.ts` — shared defaults (pagination)
- `src/utils/z-types.ts` — custom Zod helpers (e.g. query booleans)

## Patterns

- Export both Zod schemas (`CreateXSchema`) and route objects used by `initContract()`.
- Response timestamps are ISO strings (`z.string().datetime({ offset: true })`); request bodies may use `z.coerce.date()`.
- Pagination query params: `offset`, `limit` with defaults from `PAGINATION_DEFAULTS`.
- Filter params use `~cnt` suffix for contains (e.g. `"title~cnt"`).
- Use `extendZodWithOpenApi(z)` where OpenAPI metadata is needed.

## After changing contract

Rebuild dependents: `core-service`, `core-ui`, `test` all import `@total-report/core-contract/contract`.
